# Local HTML — external browser + GitHub Pages

When you create, edit, or share HTML (especially under `apps/website/`):

1. **Always run** `open "apps/website/<file>.html"` (or `npm run roadmap:open`) — not Cursor preview.
2. **Always include** both links in your reply:
   - Local: `file:///Users/sachin/Desktop/AI%20projects/God%20mode/apps/website/<file>.html`
   - Live: https://sach1ng.github.io/tandem/<file>.html
3. After edits, **commit + push** to `main` so GitHub Pages updates (see `github-pages-html.mdc`).
